HEADWORD: Turn-buckle
<hw>Turn"-buc`kle</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧rn"b⟦ucr⟧k`k'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Mech.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A loop or sleeve with a screw
thread at one end and a swivel at the other, -- used for tightening a
rod, stay, etc.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A gravitating catch, as for
fastening a shutter, the end of a chain, or a hasp.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turnbull's blue</ent>⟦br⟧
